<emphasis id="DCD6B27C4F49CFADAB2383B804E93848" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. macropetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Regel) Fr.Schmidt. It is well distinguished by simple rhizomes (rather than by the multi-headed basal part of the plant, as in 
<taxonomicName id="D436E092E3ED7240BC96C7DB1C9C8EE3" genus="T." lsidName="T. chinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="D713FF2F6C604FEBE9B4475718E9D441" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EB49A2553EF9214DD0F3F1D18208E2C8" genus="T." lsidName="T. macropetalus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="macropetalus">
<emphasis id="9087E525544EE7F8F6057AB429CAC978" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. macropetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), shorter aerial shoots, smaller flowers and shorter persistent styles (Table 
<tableCitation id="D80B203E3295265A47660E5E477A9F46" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison between Trollius austrosibiricus and related species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7">1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="8978E713FD6FE6B057A70E1D4C17942D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trollius chinensis" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="CC36AC80BC896FF7D1944763F05E5829" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Trollius chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an East Asian species occurring in Russia (Primorsky and Khabarovsk territories, Sakhalin), in the north and northeast of China and on the Korean peninsula (
<bibRefCitation id="CEB568FAFFFE9F98F2BD3F31E2605739" author="Schipczinsky, NV" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="42 - 53" refId="B12" refString="Schipczinsky, NV, 1937. Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR. Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad 7: 42 - 53" title="Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR." volume="7" year="1937">Schipczinsky 1937</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0565080848F91179DF16D3C5E24D9" author="Siplivinsky, VN" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B13" refString="Siplivinsky, VN, 1972. The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad.9: 163-182. [In Russian with Latin description]" title="The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad. 9: 163 - 182. [In Russian with Latin description]" year="1972">Siplivinsky 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F65271AD654A623155EE2F26E910EE45" author="Doroczewska, A" journalOrPublisher="Panstwowe wydawnictwo naukowe, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B4" refString="Doroczewska, A, 1974. The genus Trollius L. A taxonomical study. Monographiae botanicae. Panstwowe wydawnictwo naukowe, Warszawa" title="The genus Trollius L. A taxonomical study. Monographiae botanicae." year="1974">Doroczewska 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9AD772B923CDE071D9816BC5BCD45DF7" author="Kitagawa, M" journalOrPublisher="Gantner, Vaduz" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B8" refString="Kitagawa, M, 1979. Neo-Lineamenta Florae Manshuricae - Flora et vegetatio mundi. Gantner, Vaduz" title="Neo-Lineamenta Florae Manshuricae - Flora et vegetatio mundi." year="1979">Kitagawa 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="398FAFEA83ACC6045334AE3DADB8C29D" author="Woroshilov, VN" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B18" refString="Woroshilov, VN, 1982. Plants of the Soviet Far East. Nauka, Moscow" title="Plants of the Soviet Far East." year="1982">Woroshilov 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="34E6829AAA2B8BB3A8C2C0FEFF6448EE" author="Luferov, AN" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists, Biological series," pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="74 - 76" refId="B9" refString="Luferov, AN, 1991. New nomenclatural combinations in taxonomy of Far Eastern species of the family Ranunculaceae Juss. Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists, Biological series, 96 (5): 74 - 76" title="New nomenclatural combinations in taxonomy of Far Eastern species of the family Ranunculaceae Juss." volume="96" year="1991">Luferov 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2239241649C4C5F475E38560819C9C3A" author="Luferov, AN" journalOrPublisher="Turczaninowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 85" refId="B10" refString="Luferov, AN, 2004. A taxonomic synopsis of Ranunculaceae of the Far East of Russia. Turczaninowia 7 (1): 1 - 85" title="A taxonomic synopsis of Ranunculaceae of the Far East of Russia." volume="7" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E8928A022D58CAA5BCA2F77AE5402A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
This new species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="E7F4FD61425BA1275BE56F6AB4544A21" genus="T." lsidName="T. asiaticus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis id="E6FC3A76B36D53CB01376E4952CB30BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. by a smaller number of sepals, longer persistent styles and petals longer than sepals (Table 
<tableCitation id="D9442EF4B194EBE254EB56A588F0FAFD" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison between Trollius austrosibiricus and related species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7">1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E3CD721ACAC6CAD32F8428F31E75DF0C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trollius asiaticus" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis id="06152058136818A08A76B410633E6F2E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Trollius asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows mainly in extra-tropical Asia (Western and Eastern Siberia, Mongolia, northeast Kazakhstan and China), as well as in the northeast of European Russia (
<bibRefCitation id="22643C74189E85797CD93B43516AED9E" author="Schipczinsky, NV" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="42 - 53" refId="B12" refString="Schipczinsky, NV, 1937. Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR. Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad 7: 42 - 53" title="Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR." volume="7" year="1937">Schipczinsky 1937</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="002A1383A1922B450A0C03C359AF42EF" author="Siplivinsky, VN" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B13" refString="Siplivinsky, VN, 1972. The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad.9: 163-182. [In Russian with Latin description]" title="The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad. 9: 163 - 182. [In Russian with Latin description]" year="1972">Siplivinsky 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
